texts.orig: In active sentences, the subject is active or the subject performs the actions.
texts.text: In active sentences, the subject is active or the subject performs the actions.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: For example: The cow ( Subject ) is eating ( Verb ) grass ( Object ).-Active Voice

texts.label: text
texts.orig: In passive sentences, the subject is no longer active or the subject is acted upon by the verb.
texts.text: In passive sentences, the subject is no longer active or the subject is acted upon by the verb.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: For example: Grass ( Subject ) is being eaten ( Verb ) by the cow ( Object ). -Passive Voice
texts.text: For example: Grass ( Subject ) is being eaten ( Verb ) by the cow ( Object ). -Passive Voice
